{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633343","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633343"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17473"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17473","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17473"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10163"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70755"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10163","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10163"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17473"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56221"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5535"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23763"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23793"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70755","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70755"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman presents to discuss private health insurance options. She has recently been diagnosed with type 2 diabetes mellitus and is concerned this will affect her ability to obtain coverage.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a key feature of private health insurance regulation in Australia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Community rating system with equal premiums regardless of health status","Risk-based premium calculation for individual policy holders","Premium costs determined by individual claims history","Variable premiums based on pre-existing conditions","Higher premiums for chronic disease management"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Australian private health insurance system operates under a \u003Cstrong\u003Ecommunity rating system\u003C/strong\u003E where insurers must charge all people the same premium for the same level of cover, regardless of their age, health status, or likelihood of making claims. This promotes equity and accessibility.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERisk-based premium calculation\u003C/strong\u003E: Australian regulations prohibit insurers from charging higher premiums based on individual health risk factors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPremium costs determined by individual claims history\u003C/strong\u003E: under community rating principles, previous claims cannot influence premium costs.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVariable premiums based on pre-existing conditions\u003C/strong\u003E: while waiting periods may apply, insurers cannot charge higher premiums for pre-existing conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigher premiums for chronic disease management\u003C/strong\u003E: charging different premiums based on health conditions would breach community rating principles.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe community rating system is supported by risk equalisation arrangements between insurers to share the costs of high-risk members, and government policies like the private health insurance rebate and Lifetime Health Cover loading to encourage uptake of private insurance.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Private health insurance in Australia operates under a community rating system where insurers cannot discriminate based on health status or risk.","The private health insurance rebate is a government subsidy that reduces premium costs for eligible policy holders.","Lifetime Health Cover loading adds 2% to premiums for each year a person delays taking out private hospital cover after age 31."],"references":["About private health insurance. Department of Health and Aged Care. Available from: https://www.health.gov.au/topics/private-health-insurance/about-private-health-insurance"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56221"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17473"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56221","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56221"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:46:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T00:08:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10163"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70755"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt"